  "body": "The portfolio data layer (models, repository, report store) was complete but lacked the risk computation layer and any way for agents to consume it — requiring future agents to reimplement Sharpe, P&L, etc. from scratch.\n\n## Changes\n\n### `tradingagents/portfolio/risk_metrics.py` (new)\nPure-Python `compute_risk_metrics(snapshots, benchmark_returns=None)` over `list[PortfolioSnapshot]`:\n- Sharpe & Sortino (annualised, rf=0, downside-deviation denominator)\n- 95% VaR (historical simulation — 5th percentile)\n- Max drawdown (peak-to-trough fraction)\n- Beta (vs optional benchmark series)\n- Sector concentration (% by GICS sector from last snapshot's holdings)\n\nReturns `None` per metric when data is insufficient; stdlib/math only — no LLM, no external deps.\n\n```python\nfrom tradingagents.portfolio import compute_risk_metrics\n\nmetrics = compute_risk_metrics(snapshots, benchmark_returns=spy_daily_returns)\n# {\n#   \"sharpe\": 1.23, \"sortino\": 1.87, \"var_95\": 0.018,\n#   \"max_drawdown\": -0.142, \"beta\": 0.91,\n#   \"sector_concentration\": {\"Technology\": 35.4, ...},\n#   \"return_stats\": {\"mean_daily\": 0.0008, \"std_daily\": 0.011, \"n_days\": 90}\n# }\n```\n\n### `tradingagents/agents/utils/portfolio_tools.py` (new)\nFour `@tool`-decorated LangChain tools that expose the portfolio stack to agents — all accept/return JSON strings for LLM compatibility:\n\n| Tool | Delegates to |\n|---|---|\n| `get_enriched_holdings` | `Holding.enrich()` + `Portfolio.enrich()` — P&L, weights, cash % |\n| `compute_portfolio_risk_metrics` | `compute_risk_metrics()` from NAV history JSON |\n| `load_portfolio_risk_metrics` | `ReportStore.load_risk_metrics()` |\n| `load_portfolio_decision` | `ReportStore.load_pm_decision()` |\n\n### `tradingagents/portfolio/__init__.py`\nExports `compute_risk_metrics` as part of the public package API.\n\n### Tests\n- `tests/portfolio/test_risk_metrics.py` — 48 tests (helpers, all metrics, edge cases, type validation)\n- `tests/unit/test_portfolio_tools.py` — 19 tests (all 4 tools, invalid JSON, missing files)\n- `tests/portfolio/test_repository.py` — fixed pre-existing `ModuleNotFoundError` from absolute import of `requires_supabase` marker (redefined inline)\n\n> [!WARNING]\n>\n> <details>\n> <summary>Firewall rules blocked me from connecting to one or more addresses (expand for details)</summary>\n>\n> #### I tried to connect to the following addresses, but was blocked by firewall rules:\n>\n> - `fc.yahoo.com`\n>   - Triggering command: `/usr/bin/python3 python3 -m pytest tests/unit/ -v --tb=short` (dns block)\n>   - Triggering command: `/usr/bin/python3 python3 -m pytest tests/unit/ tests/portfolio/ -v --tb=short` (dns block)\n>   - Triggering command: `/usr/bin/python3 python3 -m pytest tests/unit/ tests/portfolio/ --tb=short -q de/node/bin/git` (dns block)\n> - `guce.yahoo.com`\n>   - Triggering command: `/usr/bin/python3 python3 -m pytest tests/unit/ -v --tb=short` (dns block)\n>   - Triggering command: `/usr/bin/python3 python3 -m pytest tests/unit/ tests/portfolio/ -v --tb=short` (dns block)\n>   - Triggering command: `/usr/bin/python3 python3 -m pytest tests/unit/ tests/portfolio/ --tb=short -q de/node/bin/git` (dns block)\n>\n> If you need me to access, download, or install something from one of these locations, you can either:\n>\n> - Configure [Actions setup steps](https://gh.io/copilot/actions-setup-steps) to set up my environment, which run before the firewall is enabled\n> - Add the appropriate URLs or hosts to the custom allowlist in this repository's [Copilot coding agent settings](https://github.com/aguzererler/TradingAgents/settings/copilot/coding_agent) (admins only)\n>\n> </details>\n\n<!-- START COPILOT ORIGINAL PROMPT -->\n\n\n\n<details>\n\n<summary>Original prompt</summary>\n\nEnhance the TradingAgents repository to ensure existing financial tools and computations (e.g., Portfolio, Holding, and Repository classes) are leveraged instead of implementing redundant functionalities from scratch. Specifically:\n\n1. Refactor the existing code to:\n   - Integrate existing risk metric calculations (Sharpe ratio, Sortino, VaR, etc.) with agents' workflows.\n   - Use the PortfolioRepository APIs for all transactional data manipulations (e.g., cash deduction, holdings updates).\n2. Modularize agents' logic to consume real-time outputs from:\n   - Risk metrics computation pipelines.\n   - Methods like `Portfolio.enrich` and `Holding.enrich` for decision-making.\n3. Pass portfolio decision data fetched via existing `load_risk_metrics` APIs into agents to ensure informed allocation strategies.\n4. Explore automation of PM agents' JSON decision files to integrate seamlessly into the current filesystem workflow.\n\nEnsure no redundant code for computations exists, and all agents interface transparently with the provided tools.\n\nThe following is the prior conversation context from the user's chat exploration (may be truncated):\n\nUser: Fiat I would like to have integration tests especially for y finance an salt centaur then a End to end test\n\nAssistant: It sounds like you'd like to add integration tests for the **Y Finance** and **Salt Centaur** components in the `TradingAgents` repository, as well as an **end-to-end test**. To achieve this:\n\n### Steps\n1. **Integration Tests**\n   - These would target the Y Finance and Salt Centaur components specifically to ensure they are functioning as expected when interacting with other components or external systems.\n   - Could you provide more information about:\n     - What aspects of Y Finance and Salt Centaur you'd like to focus on during testing (e.g., API calls, data processing)?\n     - How these components interact with other parts of your project?\n\n2. **End-to-End Tests**\n   - These tests would cover the entire workflow of your project to ensure that all components work correctly together.\n   - Could you describe the key user journey or workflow you'd like the end-to-end test to simulate?\n\n3. **Testing Framework**\n   - Are there existing tests in your project, and if so, what framework are you using (e.g., pytest, unittest)? If there isn’t one, should we start with a specific framework?\n\n4. **Pull Request (Optional)**\n   - Would you like me to create a pull request with the implementation of these tests?\n\nLet me know your preferences or further details!\n\nUser: Salt Ventura is alpha vantage , integration o. Api calls and response verification\n\nAssistant: Thanks for clarifying! Here's the plan for creating tests for your `TradingAgents` project:\n\n### 1. **Integration Tests:**\n   - **Y Finance:**\n     - Test the integration with the **Y Finance API**.\n     - Validate API calls such as fetching financial data (e.g., stock prices, historical data).\n     - Verify responses, such as checking for expected fields and data types in the API response.\n   \n   - **Salt Centaur (Alpha Vantage):**\n     - Test the integration with the **Alpha Vantage API** via Salt Centaur.\n     - Validate the API endpoints being used (e.g., fetching forex, stock market data).\n     - Include tests that verify the response structure and handle edge cases like API errors, invalid API keys, and timeouts.\n\n### 2. **End-to-End Tests:**\n   - Simulate a workflow where both *Y Finance* and *Alpha Vantage* are used together in the overall logic of the application.\n   - Ensure data from these APIs flows through your system and produces expected outputs for end users or downstream components.\n   - Validate critical user workflows:\n     - For example, monitoring a stock, analyzing trends, and displaying insights.\n\n### 3. **Testing Framework:**\n   - You can use **pytest** for its simplicity and rich ecosystem.\n   - Use mocking libraries like `unittest.mock` or `pytest-mock` to simulate API calls. This avoids hitting actual APIs during testing, which can be rate-limited or unreliable.\n\n### 4. **Next Steps:**\n   Would you like me to:\n   - Add boilerplate test files and open a pull request to get started?\n   - Provide code examples for these tests?\n   - Assist in setting up the testing framework in your repository?\n\nLet me know!\n\nUser: Create a pr\n\nAssistant: A pull request has been created to add integration and end-to-end tests for Y Finance and Salt Centaur in your repository. You can review the PR and provide feedback as needed! Let me know if further modifications are required.\n\nUser: Not salt centaur , alpha centaur\n\nAssistant: Thank you for clarifying! The focus will now be on **Alpha Centaur** (your integration with Alpha Vantage). Here's the updated plan:\n\n### Updated Plan for Tests:\n1. **Integration Tests:**\n   - **Y Finance:**\n     - Verify fetching financial data such as stock prices, historical price data, etc., through the Y Finance API.\n     - Mock the API calls and ensure valid data structure ...\n\n</details>\n\n\n\n<!-- START COPILOT CODING AGENT SUFFIX -->\n\n*This pull request was created from Copilot chat.*\n>\n\n<!-- START COPILOT CODING AGENT TIPS -->\n---\n\n💬 Send tasks to Copilot coding agent from [Slack](https://gh.io/cca-slack-docs) and [Teams](https://gh.io/cca-teams-docs) to turn conversations into code. Copilot posts an update in your thread when it's finished.",
